To make the illustration design better for a children's audience, you can modify the style attribute as follows:

position: relative;
top: 50%;
left: 50%;
transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
box-sizing: border-box;
padding: 20px;
border: 1px solid #000;
border-radius: 10px;
background-color: #f5f5f5;
display: block;
width: 300px;
height: 300px;
min-width: initial;
max-width: initial;
min-height: initial;
max-height: initial;

Explanation:
- Changed the position to "relative" to position the illustration element relative to its normal position.
- Added "transform: translate(-50%, -50%);" to center the element horizontally and vertically using the percentage values.
- Increased the padding to 20px for better spacing inside the element.
- Added a 1px solid black border with a border-radius of 10px for a rounded appearance.
- Set a light grey background color using "background-color: #f5f5f5;".
- Specified a fixed width and height of 300px each to define the size of the illustration.
- Reset the min-width, max-width, min-height, and max-height properties to their initial values to allow the element to scale freely based on children's browser screen.

Feel free to adjust the values according to your specific requirements and preferences.
